nsider.com%2Fdonald-trump%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Elon%20Musk%20have%20both%20called%20for%20the%20impeachment%20of%20federal%20judges.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20would%20take%20a%20majority%20vote%20in%20the%20House%20and%20a%20two-thirds%20vote%20in%20the%20Senate%20to%20convict%20a%20judge.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELegal%20experts%20say%20the%20threats%20are%20just%20one%20way%20the%20White%20House%20is%20trying%20to%20undercut%20the%20judiciary.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%20want%20to%20impeach%20federal%20judges%20that%20stand%20in%20their%20way.%20History%20shows%20there%20is%20little%20chance%20of%20that%20happening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20Trump%20wrote%20on%20Truth%20Social%20that%20a%20judge%20who%20fit%20US%20District%20Judge%20James%20Boasberg's%20description%20%26quot%3Bshould%20be%20IMPEACHED!!!%26quot%3B%20Trump%20and%20his%20allies%20have%20expressed%20fury%20that%20a%20Boasberg%20order%20restricted%20his%20deportation%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20earlier%2C%20Musk%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Felonmusk%2Fstatus%2F1889711960729522180%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20February%2012%2C%20%26quot%3BImpeach%20this%20activist%20posing%20as%20a%20judge!%20Such%20a%20person%20does%20great%20discredit%20to%20the%20American%20justice%20system.%26quot%3B%20The%20message%20quoted%20criticism%20of%20US%20District%20Judge%20John%20J.%20McConnell%20Jr.%2C%20who%20had%20temporarily%20blocked%20the%20administration's%20funding%20freeze.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepublicans'%20efforts%20are%20likely%20trying%20to%20grind%20down%20views%20of%20the%20federal%20judiciary%2C%20according%20to%20Indiana%20University%20law%20professor%20Charles%20Geyh.%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20Trump%20may%20ultimately%20wish%20to%20open%20the%20door%20to%20defying%20court%20orders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20trace%20the%20arc%20of%20this%20story%2C%20the%20arc%20so%20far%20would%20seem%20to%20lead%20you%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20saying%2C%20'well%2C%20ok%2C%20shrug%20this%20off%2C%20this%20is%20just%20yet%20another%20feeble%20attempt%20at%20impeaching%20judges%20that%20has%20never%20worked%20and%20certainly%20never%20advanced%20in%20a%20hundred%20years%2C'%26quot%3B%20Geyh%2C%20an%20expert%20on%20judicial%20ethics%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20context%20is%20different%2C%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BPresident%20Trump%20is%20going%20after%20the%20judiciary%20in%20multiple%20ways%20simultaneously.%26quot%3B%20His%20playbook%20is%20%26quot%3Boverwhelm%20them%2C%20it's%20potentially%20defy%20their%20orders%2C%20and%20it's%20threaten%20them%20with%20impeachment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20and%20the%20White%20House%20have%20repeatedly%20said%20he%20won't%20defy%20federal%20court%20orders.%20It%20remains%20contested%20if%20the%20administration%20ignored%20US%20District%20Judge%20James%20Boasberg's%20order%20last%20weekend%20to%20temporarily%20halt%20deportations%20under%20the%201789%20Alien%20Enemies%20Act%20which%20Trump%20formally%20invoked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERequests%20for%20comment%20to%20the%20White%20House%20and%20Musk%20from%20BI%20went%20unanswered.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20and%20Musk%20have%20hammered%20judges%20throughout%20the%20past%20week%2C%20particularly%20Boasberg.%20White%20House%20press%20secretary%20Karoline%20Leavitt%20also%20called%20out%20Boasberg's%20wife's%20political%20donations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e74667b1-486c-465e-9427-f4164645e8cf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EChief%20Justice%20Roberts%20has%20tried%20to%20calm%20the%20waters%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchief-justice-warns-of-threats-against-judicial-independence-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJohn%20Roberts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20appointed%20by%20Republican%20President%20George%20W.%20Bush%2C%20tried%20to%20stop%20the%20tide%20by%20releasing%20a%20rare%20statement%20decrying%20judicial%20impeachments%20after%20Trump%20endorsed%20removing%20Boasberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20more%20than%20two%20centuries%2C%20it%20has%20been%20established%20that%20impeachment%20is%20not%20an%20appropriate%20response%20to%20disagreement%20concerning%20a%20judicial%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20Roberts%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20normal%20appellate%20review%20process%20exists%20for%20that%20purpose.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20said%20he%20respected%20Roberts'%20views.%20Yet%20a%20day%20later%2C%20the%20president's%20political%20operation%20sent%20an%20email%20that%20linked%20to%20a%20fundraising%20page%20with%20the%20subject%20line%2C%20%26quot%3BImpeach%2C%20Impeach%2C%20Impeach.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAm%20I%20right%20friend%3F%20%E2%80%94%20Should%20deranged%2C%20power-hungry%20judges%20who%20let%20violent%20criminals%20roam%20free%20%E2%80%94%20putting%20your%20life%20and%20your%20family%20in%20grave%20danger%20%E2%80%94%20be%20impeached%3F%26quot%3B%20the%20email%2C%20signed%20by%20Trump%2C%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20threshold%20to%20impeach%20and%20remove%20an%20official%20is%20high%2C%20which%20Trump%20knows%20well%2C%20having%20been%20acquitted%20by%20the%20Senate%20a%20record%20two%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20for%20impeaching%20a%20judge%20mirrors%20that%20of%20a%20presidential%20impeachment.%20Charges%20must%20originate%20in%20the%20US%20House%20of%20Representatives.%20If%20a%20majority%20of%20lawmakers%20vote%20to%20impeach%20a%20judge%2C%20their%20charges%20are%20then%20forwarded%20to%20the%20Senate.%20It%20ultimately%20takes%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20Senate%2C%20or%2067%20senators%2C%20to%20convict%20a%20judge%20of%20impeachment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepublicans%20only%20hold%2053%20seats%20in%20the%20Senate.%20It's%20unlikely%20that%20enough%20Democrats%20would%20support%20such%20a%20measure%20to%20reach%20the%20threshold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2230ba9549-5ac4-479b-8d22-299e8bb3b224%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EOnly%2014%20judges%20have%20been%20impeached%20throughout%20history%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHouse%20lawmakers%20have%20impeached%2014%20federal%20judges%20and%20one%20Supreme%20Court%20justice%2C%20Samuel%20Chase%2C%20throughout%20history.%20Of%20those%2015%2C%20only%20eight%20have%20been%20convicted.%20Former%20District%20Judge%20G.%20Thomas%20Porteous%2C%20Jr.%20was%20the%20last%20federal%20judge%20impeached.%20Lawmakers%20charged%20Porteous%20in%202010%20with%20accepting%20bribes%20and%20committing%20perjury.%20He%20was%20later%20convicted%20and%20removed%20from%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeyh%20said%20that%20in%20early%20American%20history%2C%20some%20leaders%20tried%20to%20go%20after%20judges%20for%20their%20rulings.%20While%20threats%20cropped%20up%20at%20times%2C%20politicians%20began%20to%20respect%20that%20there%20were%20limits%20to%20their%20responses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOver%20time%2C%20this%20norm%20developed%20that%20judicial%20independence%20requires%20that%20we%20not%20go%20after%20judges%20because%20we%20disagree%20with%20their%20decisions%2C%20even%20if%20we%20think%20they%20are%20high-handed%2C%20even%20if%20we%20think%20they%20are%20activists%2C%26quot%3B%20Geyh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFederal%20judges%20who%20receive%20lifetime%20appointments%20also%20cannot%20be%20removed%20from%20office%20without%20impeachment.%20There%20is%20also%20no%20official%20retirement%20age%2C%20though%20judges%20are%20eventually%20eligible%20to%20take%20senior%20status%2C%20a%20semi-form%20of%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImpeaching%20a%20judge%20for%20a%20decision%20would%20be%20a%20significant%20escalatory%20step%2C%20said%20Michael%20J.%20Gerhardt%2C%20a%20constitutional%20law%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20North%20Carolina%20School%20of%20Law%20in%20Chapel%20Hill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20over%20200%20years%2C%20no%20federal%20judge%20has%20ever%20been%20impeached%20and%20removed%20from%20office%20based%20on%20their%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20Gerhardt%2C%20who%20has%20written%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnyupress.org%2F9781479824717%2Fthe-law-of-presidential-impeachment%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20book%20about%20the%20history%20of%20impeachmen%3C%2Fa%3Et%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20one%2C%20and%20that%20tells%20us%20something.%20Impeachment%20is%20not%20the%20appropriate%20process%20to%20use%20if%20you%20disagree%20with%20what%20a%20judge%20rules.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-musk-judges-impeachment-likely-empty-threat-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742657770000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67dddd4a63d72727e197fc68%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-musk-judges-impeachment-likely-empty-threat-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Like%20impeaching%20and%20convicting%20a%20president%2C%20there%20is%20a%20high%20bar%20to%20cross%20to%20remove%20a%20federal%20judge%20from%20the%20bench%2C%20despite%20Donald%20Trump's%20calls.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bgriffiths%40insider.com%20(Brent%20D.%20Griffiths)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A320%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-musk-judges-impeachment-likely-empty-threat-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump%20revokes%20security%20clearance%20for%20Harris%2C%20Clinton%2C%20and%20critics%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742657665000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F2aad%2Flive%2F7067aed0-06f6-11f0-97d3-37df2b293ed1